To get to the grocery store that is 1km away in Thailand, you have a few options:

1. Walking: If the weather is pleasant and you enjoy walking, you can simply walk to the grocery store. It will take you approximately 10-15 minutes to cover a distance of 1km.

2. Cycling: If you have a bicycle or can rent one, cycling can be a convenient and quick way to reach the grocery store. It will take you around 5-10 minutes to cover the distance.

3. Motorbike: If you are comfortable riding a motorbike, you can use it to reach the grocery store. Motorbikes are a popular mode of transportation in Thailand, and you can easily rent one if you don't own one yourself. It will take you just a few minutes to reach the store.

4. Tuk-tuk: Tuk-tuks are three-wheeled vehicles commonly used for short-distance transportation in Thailand. You can easily find a tuk-tuk near your location and negotiate a fare to take you to the grocery store. It might be slightly more expensive than other options, but it can be a fun and convenient way to travel.

5. Taxi: Taxis are widely available in Thailand, especially in urban areas. You can hail a taxi or use a ride-hailing app to book one. Taxis are metered, so make sure the driver uses the meter or agrees on a fare before starting the journey.
